title: For Sale:  2 Boxes- BRAND NEW BLANK 9mm Rounds- BLANKS ONLY!
location: Fort myers/cape/ lee county, South West Florida, Florida
postcontent:
Hey folks I have 2 boxes of Fiocchi 9mm Salve blank rounds, 100 in total (50 per box)

Blank rounds are used in movies/tv/etc and "simulated" live fire training which is basically the look, feel and sound of a real round except a projectile ejecting from the barrel. These bullets are as loud and in some case as dangerous so you still should follow all safety precautions as if these were live rounds. 

Besides films, blanks are also used by some home owners as an alternative to deadly force as these can be fired in a attempt to frighten and scare of potential intruders. Blanks also produce the same exact muzzle flash a regular live round would; once again the only difference is there isn't a bullet that fires out of the barrel.

Contact justin @ REDACTED if interested. I will cut a nice deal if you purchase both boxes. Thanks in advance.

 It comes with a  green rope lanyard, a military flap style holster with shoulder strap that is in very good shape which is made of a a weatherproof woven vinyl in an OD green color. The holster has room for the pistol, a supply of flare cartridges and miscellaneous items. Holster is in good but well used condition.

Also included is a set of chamber adapters. The first allows you to fire any .22LR, Long or Short ammunition. The other is for firing .410 shotgun shells or .45 Long Colt ammo. The adapters are a simple drop in installation and they have rifled barrels making them legal to use anywhere a real handgun is alllowed. Bottom line is that these turn this flare pistol into an excellent emergency self defense/survival tool for your "bug out" bag.

Finally there is a complete cleaning kit that has a stiff nylon brush for normal cleaning. A brass bristle brush for really heavy duty cleaning and a felt tipped rod that fits the bore snuggly eliminating the need for cleaning patches.

What I am offering up for sale is a '70 Series 1911A1 United States Marine Corps Commemorative Colt in .45 automatic.  This Colt is in new, mint and unfired condition. The Presentation case has a brass plaque that reads "United States Marine Corp, Limited Edition".  The box is in excellent condition with the key still in the original white envelope. "GLOCK’s original (pre-ban) magazines were NFML (non-full metal lined).
